    "body": "### Problem\n\nSo i have these mappings to move blocks of selected text down/up\n\n```lua\nmap(\"v\", \"J\", \":m '>+1<CR>gv=gv\", { desc = \"Move selected blocks down\" })\nmap(\"v\", \"K\", \":m '<-2<CR>gv=gv\", { desc = \"Move selected blocks up\" })\n```\n\nThey previously worked fine, but recently (i dont remember exactly when) they stopped re-selecting moved blocks. So i narrowed down the problem to the following minimal `init.lua`\n\n```lua\nlocal map = vim.keymap.set\n\nlocal function toggle_bars()\n  vim.o.cmdheight = vim.o.cmdheight ~= 0 and 0 or 1\nend\n\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd(\"VimEnter\", {\n  callback = function()\n    -- Disable bars by default\n    toggle_bars()\n  end,\n})\n\nmap(\"v\", \"J\", \":m '>+1<CR>gv=gv\", { desc = \"Move selected blocks down\" })\nmap(\"v\", \"K\", \":m '<-2<CR>gv=gv\", { desc = \"Move selected blocks up\" })\n```\n\nThe problem is that when i select 2 or 1 line in visual mode, those mapping move text and correctly re-select the moved blocks. But when i select 3 or more lines in a block, they do not re-select anything, just enter visual mode at cursor position. Heres the screencast:\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/7897df40-3da3-4a1b-b7a0-3db2588a51b2\n\nThis was even reported on reddit, though i didnt find anything in neovim issues\nhttps://www.reddit.com/r/neovim/comments/17776xa/moving_blocks_of_code_up_and_down/\n\nWeird thing that it only stops working when i hide command-line\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n It also stops working when i manually do all the steps\n\n```bash\n# open file\nnvim --clean\n# hide command-line \n:set cmdheight=0\n# create mapping\n:vmap J :m '>+1<CR>gv=gv\n# move text and observe the same behavior\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nAfter moving blocks of code, visually re-select the moved lines at their new position\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-2538+g63594ffa04\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty 0.16.1 (42f49eeb)\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nalacritty\n\n### Installation\n\naur",
